  "text": "TAP purification was performed essentially as described [CITATION_1] . Shortly, 12 l of the Pch1-TAP strain were grown to an optical density (OD) of 0.5 (5.5 Â10 6 cells per ml), pelleted and frozen in liquid nitrogen by passing the pellet through a 50-ml syringe to produce 'noodles'. The extract was obtained using an electrical mortar/pestle (Reich RM100) under liquid nitrogen. The following steps were as described [CITATION_2] . Aliquots of the elution product were separated on Novex gradient gels and silver stained (Silver Quest, Invitrogen). The protein bands were cut from the gel, destained and extracted, followed by dialysis into ammonium bicarbonate. After trypsination, peptides were analysed by MS-MS and resulting data were compared with the fission yeast proteome. For the co-IP in Figure 1B , extracts from a 100 ml culture volume were prepared as described above.",
